00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:17.337
I was first exhibited in 1884,

00:00:17.337 --> 00:00:20.010
and I caused quite a stir in Paris

00:00:20.010 --> 00:00:22.830
because although my artist intended for me

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:27.540
to be a study in light and
shade, audiences and critics

00:00:27.540 --> 00:00:31.290
thought I was trying to
be sexually provocative.

00:00:31.290 --> 00:00:32.463
So, which is it?

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:37.050
What does the artwork mean?

00:00:37.050 --> 00:00:39.000
Now, you might be sitting
there thinking, "Well,

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.090
it's subjective, there's
no right or wrong answer!"

00:00:42.090 --> 00:00:45.960
but I am willing to bet that
you don't really believe that.

00:00:45.960 --> 00:00:49.080
There's a big difference
between saying that the quality

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:53.820
of an artwork is subjective
and the meaning is subjective.

00:00:53.820 --> 00:00:56.220
If you don't like The
Portrait of Madame X"

00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:59.190
then fair enough, I guess
I'm not to everyone's taste.

00:00:59.190 --> 00:01:00.930
And I suppose when I pose for it,

00:01:00.930 --> 00:01:03.420
it's more like "The Portrait of Madame XY,"

00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:07.950
but is it really the case
that I can be about anything?

00:01:07.950 --> 00:01:10.800
If somebody says to you, I
just saw "Doctor Strange 2".

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:12.270
And you go, "Oh yeah, what's it about?"

00:01:12.270 --> 00:01:15.270
And they say, "It's about how
love has an everlasting value,

00:01:15.270 --> 00:01:17.580
even between two people of
different social classes

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:19.233
on a doomed ocean liner."

00:01:20.850 --> 00:01:23.340
You'd be like, "No, that's Titanic."

00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:25.991
It definitely seems like you
can look at a work of art,

00:01:25.991 --> 00:01:30.540
think you know what
it's about and be wrong,

00:01:30.540 --> 00:01:34.560
which means the meaning at
least is not subjective.

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:39.210
So assuming artworks do
have objective meaning,

00:01:39.210 --> 00:01:41.820
