or you might miss out

00:10:16.740 --> 00:10:19.050
on what the art really has to offer!

00:10:19.050 --> 00:10:21.270
The philosopher Susan Sontag

00:10:21.270 --> 00:10:24.870
says we should stop
trying to interpret art,

00:10:24.870 --> 00:10:28.670
stop trying to get it
and just experience it.

00:10:28.670 --> 00:10:31.080
Like Duchamp's "Fountain".

00:10:31.080 --> 00:10:33.420
Everybody says, "Oh,
he's making a statement

00:10:33.420 --> 00:10:35.790
about the art world!" and
Picasso's paintings,

00:10:35.790 --> 00:10:38.550
everyone says, "Oh, he's
asking the big questions,

00:10:38.550 --> 00:10:43.550
like... what if there was a
really f*****d up looking woman?"

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:47.520
But art isn't a statement or a question.

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:49.980
If it was, the artist
would just write it down.

00:10:49.980 --> 00:10:53.760
Art isn't philosophy
with pictures, it's art!

00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:58.760
So turn off Brain and tune in
to the aesthetic experience!

